## Latest Feature: 用户/商家小程序合并

### Backend

- Added multi-identity account support with `AccountIdentity`, `MerchantProfile`, `MerchantStore`, `MerchantStoreMembership`, `MerchantStorePermission`, `MerchantNotification`, and `MerchantOrderVerification`.
- `auth` APIs now return unified `session_context` and merchant profile data for login routing, dual-identity role selection, and role switching.
- Added merchant-facing APIs in `backend/app/api/merchant.py` for store listing, dashboard, order verification, verification records, notifications, and merchant profile.
- Added admin merchant management APIs in `backend/app/api/admin_merchant.py` for store maintenance, merchant/staff account creation, updates, permission assignment, and bulk import.
- Added backend regression coverage in `backend/tests/test_merchant.py` for dual-identity creation, merchant login context, order verification, and verification record queries.

### Admin Web

- Added `商家管理 -> 门店管理` and `商家管理 -> 商家账号` menus in the admin layout.
- Added store management page for creating, editing, enabling, and disabling merchant stores.
- Added merchant account management page for owner/staff maintenance, dual-identity setup, store binding, module permission configuration, and batch import.

### Mini Program

- Merged original user mini program and merchant verification mini program into the single `miniprogram` project.
- Added role-aware login flow: unauthenticated users default to the user homepage, single-role accounts enter directly, dual-identity accounts choose role after login.
- Added role switching, store selection, no-permission guidance, merchant message center, and custom tab bar support.
- Converted the four main tab pages into role containers so user and merchant experiences stay isolated while sharing the same account/login framework.
- Merchant mode now requires store selection on each entry and keeps orders, messages, and profile data isolated from user mode.

## Latest Feature: 短信验证码登录接入腾讯云

### Backend

- Integrated Tencent Cloud SMS SDK (`tencentcloud-sdk-python`) for sending real SMS verification codes.
- Added `backend/app/services/sms_service.py` — async `send_sms(phone, code)` function that calls Tencent Cloud SMS API; falls back to no-op with warning when SecretId/SecretKey are not configured.
- Updated `backend/app/core/config.py` — added `TENCENT_SMS_SECRET_ID`, `TENCENT_SMS_SECRET_KEY`, `TENCENT_SMS_SDK_APP_ID`, `TENCENT_SMS_SIGN_NAME`, `TENCENT_SMS_TEMPLATE_ID`, `TENCENT_SMS_APP_KEY` settings.
- Updated `POST /api/auth/sms-code` endpoint: added 60-second rate limiting per phone number (HTTP 429), calls Tencent Cloud SMS to send real SMS, removed plain-text code from response body.
- Added 6 new test cases in `backend/tests/test_auth.py` covering rate limiting, response format, wrong code rejection, auto-registration, and existing user login.
- Updated `backend/tests/conftest.py` with `latest_sms_code` fixture to read verification codes from DB (since response no longer returns them).

### Mini Program / Flutter APP / H5

- No code changes needed — all three clients already had SMS login UI and API calls in place. The backend SMS integration makes them fully functional.

